										i.fas.fa-kiss
									h4.principle-title KISS
								p.principle-description KISS stands for 'Keep It Simple, Stupid!'.  The temptation with all these available languages/frameworks/tools is to over-complicate. To avoid this, I carefully plan my projects before writing any code. Everything is there for a purpose.
							div.principle
								span.principle-head
									span.principle-icon
										i.fas.fa-sun
									h4.principle-title D.R.Y.
								p.principle-description DRY stands for 'Don't Repeat Yourself'.  Without careful planning, code can quickly become repetitious and therefore a nightmare to maintain!  I ensure that any changes/updates to functionality need only to be made in one place.
							div.principle
								span.principle-head
									span.principle-icon
										i.fas.fa-socks
									h4.principle-title S.O.C.
								p.principle-description SOC stands for 'Separation of Concerns'.  From a maintenance and scalability perspective, it is very important to separate concerns by modularising code.  This allows making efficient changes to apps without breaking everything!
							div.principle
